<br>
No, because they still need to post for that date at the same time as everyone else.  To get a 7/21, date for example, so they can get a 7/22 4 am raid they still need to post along with everyone else on 7/7.  If they don't get the post in time starting 7/7 they effectively can't raid on 7/22 4 am.  So they get no advantage. They are still competing for the same date at the same time as everyone else.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> In doing so the plane sits there unraided for a full day because Zenith's claimed that date but actually raiding the next day...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
No, the amount of spawns killed is still the same.<br>
<br>
If Zenith has 7/21 reserved and raids at 4 am 7/22 then you have:<br>
<br>
7/20 Guild x raid clears plane<br>
7/21 no raid to allow full repop (or even an early raid done with Zenith's permission)<br>
7/22 4am Zenith clears plane<br>
7/22 7pm Guild y raid clears plane.<br>
<br>
So from 7/20 to 7/22 you have at least 3 possibly 4 clearings.  This is the same as if we had a 7/20, 7/21, 7/22 raid all starting at 6pm.<br>
<br>
This compromise was done to allow Zenith to have a full spawned plane instead of their normally empty plane for the first 3 hours they show up and then have repops for the rest of the day and never get a full plane pop before they have to leave.  It only slightly inconveniences the Guild Y raid as half the plane will already be popped by starting time.<br>
<br>
If a raid wants to go to Fear in between Guild x and Zenith and can start early enough so that Zenith has a full pop by 4 am then Zenith can allow them to go ahead thus adding an additional clearing but that is up to Zenith to decide. <p><A HREF="http://www.silentredemption.org/" TARGET="_new">
